description.narrative: New strategic evidence on the situation of children is available for the Middle East and North Africa to inform national policies, programmes and national and regional advocacy. This strategic evidence focuses on the learning losses generated by the COVID-19 crisis, COVID-19 vaccine acceptance and prevention behaviours, the evolving situation of women and girls, and UNICEF&39;s emergency preparedness work in the region. MENARO completed two multi-country evaluations on UNICEF&39;s work on eliminating violence against children and UNICEF&39;s response to COVID-19 in MENA. Most of the reports finalized in 2021 are the results of the cooperation with other United Nations agencies. | Status:Met | As-of Date:23/03/2022
